#http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/Seared-Asian-Steak-and-Mushrooms-on-Mixed-Greens-with-Ginger-Dressing-361612
IN	2 tablespoons soy sauce
IN	2 tablespoons seasoned rice vinegar
IN	4 1/2 teaspoons vegetable oil, divided
IN	1 tablespoon minced peeled fresh ginger
IN	1/2 teaspoon Asian chili-garlic sauce
IN	1/8 teaspoon plus 2 teaspoons Asian sesame oil, divided
IN	1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro
IN	2 12-ounce rib-eye steaks
IN	2 tablespoons toasted sesame seeds
IN	8 ounces crimini (baby bella) mushrooms, quartered
IN	8 cups mixed greens
PR	Mix soy sauce, rice vinegar, 1 1/2 teaspoons vegetable oil, minced ginger, chili-garlic sauce, and 1/8 teaspoon sesame oil in small bowl. Add cilantro and stir to blend. Set dressing aside.
PR	Rub 1/4 teaspoon sesame oil over each side of each rib-eye steak. Sprinkle steaks with salt, pepper, and toasted sesame seeds; press firmly to adhere. Heat 2 teaspoons vegetable oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; sauté until browned, about 8 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer sautéed mushrooms to plate. Add 1 teaspoon vegetable oil and 1 teaspoon sesame oil to skillet; heat over medium-high heat. Add steaks; cook to desired doneness, 3 to 4 minutes per side for medium-rare. Transfer steaks to cutting board. Slice steaks. Toss mixed greens with dressing in large bowl; divide greens among plates. Top with steak slices and mushrooms and serve.
